routeFacts.name: Tharandter Rampe
routeFacts.description: Tharandter Rampe is a German route developed by Dovetail Games, running for 79 kilometres between Dresden and Chemnitz. This route includes DB BR 612 and DB BR 143, both in DB Traffic red livery. The route also features the DB BR 363 “V 60“ diesel shunter, and Railpool BR 185.6 on freight duties. The G6 is also due to sub in.
routeInfo: Built in sections throughout the mid-19th Century, the line between Dresden and Chemnitz faced treacherous terrain, gradients as steep as 2.6% were constructed through the valleys between Freiburg and Dresden making for a treacherous climb and descent for rail traffic. The line has also seen many sections rebuilt over the years to account for increasing demand and congestion. As of 2012, the line was already electrified, however was still served by diesel traction to connect with unelectrified lines beyond Chemnitz.
